<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
  <body>
    <div metal:fill-slot="body">
      <h1>Help us improve</h1>
      <p>
        Launchpad is a work in progress, and we welcome your feedback on how
        to make it better. File bugs, talk to us on the IRC channel
        #launchpad on irc.freenode.net, or send us email. If you have ideas
        for new features, take a look at the
        <a href="https://wiki.launchpad.canonical.com/">Launchpad Wiki</a>
        and add a specification, then work with us on #launchpad to get it
        implemented.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            The best way to report problems in Launchpad is in the Malone bug tracker. You can report bugs about:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <a href="/products/malone/+bugs">Malone itself</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/products/rosetta/+bugs">Rosetta</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/products/foaf/+bugs">Launchpad accounts and teams</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/products/doap/+bugs">product and project registration</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/products/soyuz/+bugs">distribution and package registration</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="/products/launchpad/+bugs">any other aspect of Launchpad</a>.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            If a problem in Launchpad is preventing you from reporting bugs,
            <a href="mailto:launchpad-error-reports@lists.canonical.com">tell us the problem by e-mail</a>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            If you have general questions or suggestions,
            <a href="irc://irc.freenode.net/#launchpad">join us on IRC</a> &#8212;
            network <code>irc.freenode.net</code>,
            channel <code>#launchpad</code>.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Thanks for helping us make Launchpad a great place to develop software.
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
